title: JFK Declassified - Tracking Oswald (720p) Part 1-7 Complete
description:
JFK Declassified: Tracking Oswald is a 2017 History Channel television documentary series about an investigation led by former CIA agent Robert Baer and former LAPD police lieutenant Adam Bercovici into the 1963 assassination of U.S. president John F. Kennedy. They used recently declassified government documents to track down locations and witnesses connected with Lee Harvey Oswald, the suspected assassin.

In most countries, episodes 1-6 aired between April 25th and May 30th, 2017. But, in the USA, episodes 3-6 were delayed until 16 September 2017. The History Channel must have been coerced to delay or cancel the broadcasts of those four episodes.

On 26 October 2017, an additional 2,891 secret files concerning the JFK assassination were declassified and released by the United States Federal Government. Robert Baer and his team then examined these new files and presented his findings and updated conclusions in episode 7, which aired on 19 December 2017. Enjoy!
